May 4 2002
----------
 Build 44:
 ---------
 + Message-Id saving when sending. Works only on SMTP severs that return
   the Message-ID after sending the message.
   For this to work you need to manually set the following registry entries:
   (HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Far\Plugins\FARMail\Common)
   SaveMessageID = dword:00000000 or dword:00000001 (off/on)
   MessageIDTemplate = "Some text %s"

   The MessageIDTemplate is the template for extracting Message-Id from SMTP response
   (e.g. "250 Message received: %s")
 * Reply.fms updated to save all references.

   This in original mail:

   References: <sdfdsfs@sdsad>
    <sdfdsfs@sdfdsf>
    <sdfsdfdwee@sdf>

   Turns to this after reply:

   References: <sdfdsfs@sdsad> <sdfdsfs@sdfdsf> <sdfsdfdwee@sdf> <msg-id>
 + DecodeUUE() (uue.cpp), now needs to be inserted into DecodeField().
 ! Function DecodeField did not return any value.
   

